<h3>Privacy Policy</h3>
<p>La Trobe University collects information for the purpose of identifying and contacting users of AHAD. This information is stored securely and will not be released to other AHAD users nor to third parties for any reason, except where the user chooses to publish that information when depositing records.</p>
<p>The user may choose whether or not to reveal their contact details at the point of deposition, or remove or edit them at a later date.
Data about individual users’ usage of AHAD is not logged or stored.  The total number of visits and number of downloads of individual resources is logged and can me made available on request.
It is the responsibility of the Depositor to seek permission to publish the names and contact details of Creators. If your contact details have been published without your consent, contact the Depositor. If their contact details are not available or you do not receive an immediate response contact the AHAD Editor.</p>
<h3>Rights Policy</h3>
<p>Users are responsible for observing the copyright, intellectual property and other rights retained by the Rights Holder identified on the Resource Record. Depositors are responsible for accurately describing the Rights Holder and seeking the permission of the Rights Holder to publish the Resource under the AHAD Conditions of Use and any other license or Rights statement they wish to use. Depositors are responsible for retaining records of such agreements. 
La Trobe University does not take any responsibility for verifying the accuracy of Rights Holders or Rights Statements as reported in AHAD, nor does it take responsibility for infringements of those rights by Users. </p>
<h3>Take-down policy</h3>
<p>In the event that La Trobe University is alerted to an alleged breech of copyright or IP we will Embargo the resource until the matter has been resolved. The following steps will be followed:
<ul>
<li>The Depositor will be informed of the complaint and asked to respond.</li>
<li>The Rights Holder will be contacted, wherever possible.</li>
<li>The matter will be referred to the Editorial Board who will recommend whether the Resource be reinstated (with or without redaction)</li>
</ul></p>
<h3>Editorial Policy</h3>
<p>Records created by Depositors are considered to be their own work and their own responsibility and depositors are best placed to describe their own work. However, some elements of the record, particularly the creation or selection or keywords require reference to similar resources described by other depositors. AHAD editors share the responsibility to maintain consistency in these terms wherever possible.
Individual records may be edited by the User who created the record, and any other User to whom they granted Access Rights. Only the individual who created the record can delete it.
The AHAD Site Administrator and AHAD Editor has/have the technical ability to access any individual record (in Draft and Active status), but will only do so in the following circumstances:</p>
<ul>
<li>if requested by the User who created the record, or a User with Access Rights, in order to provide technical assistance;</li>
<li>to embargo a Resource or Record suspected of breeching the Conditions of Use;</li>
<li>to delete a Resource or Record found to be in breech of the Conditions of Use, or reinstate one found to be compliant.</li>
</ul>
<p>In addition, AHAD reserves the right to edit keywords to make them consistent with usage in the majority of records.  In the event that this is necessary: </p>
<ul>
<li>changes will only be made to keywords with unequivocal synonyms or variations in spelling; and</li>
<li>the user will be notified of the changes. </li>
</ul>
<p>If more complex changes are required, e.g. to Site Name keywords, the AHAD editor will liaise with the User prior to making changes.</p>